                     <origDate notBefore="1398" notAfter="1438">The Metropolitan ʾabbā Bärtolomewos is mentioned on <locus target="#9r">9r</locus>. Bärtolomewos came to Ethiopia in 1398/99 A.D. as a successor of ʾabuna salāma II “the Translator” and died around 1438. Kahǝn Mäksimos may be identical to ʿaqabe säʿat Mäksimos (s. EAE II, 30a).</origDate>
